Peel and chop the @onion{1} and @carrot{1} into roughly 1cm pieces. Peel and grate all but one of the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Slice the @aubergine{1} into discs approximately 1cm thick.

Add a splash of @oil{a splash} to a #saucepan{} on medium heat, add your onion and cook for ~{5%mins} until soft, then add your carrot and grated garlic and cook for a further ~{3%mins}. Add the @lamb mince{250%g} along with the @cinnamon stick{1}. Stir and cook until your lamb has browned, then add the @chopped tomatoes{1%tin}. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch}, a good grind of @black pepper{} and a sprinkle of @?sugar{a sprinkle}. Gently simmer your lamb mixture for ~{15-20%mins} until it is thick and tomatoey.

While your lamb mixture is simmering, preheat your #grill{} to high. Pop your aubergine on a #baking tray{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{a drizzle}, a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{} and grill for ~{8-9%mins} on one side and ~{8-9%mins} on the other side, remove from your grill and leave to the side (leave your grill on).

> The aubergine slices should be slightly browned and soft, if they aren't soft, cook them for a little longer. If they are getting browned too quickly, turn the heat down a little.

You can also prepare the @ciabatta{1} while your lamb mixture is simmering and the aubergine is grilling! Cut the ciabatta into slices about 1cm thick and leave to the side.

When your lamb mixture is nice and thick, remove your cinnamon stick and pour into an #ovenproof dish{}. Lay your aubergine on top and spoon over the @crème fraîche{1}. Spread your crème fraîche with the back of a #spoon{} and then grate over the @parmesan cheese{20%g}. Put the dish under your grill for ~{5%mins} or until the top is bubbling and brown.

While your moussaka is browning, put the @wild rocket{1} in a #bowl{}, drizzle over a splash of @olive oil{a splash} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{} and toss.

Once brown, remove your moussaka from your grill and pop your ciabatta slices under for ~{2%mins} on each side.

> Watch they don't burn!

Cut the remaining garlic clove in half, take your ciabatta out from under your grill and rub your garlic clove across each slice. You can also drizzle over a little @?olive oil{a little}.

Serve your moussaka with your rocket and garlic ciabatta on the side.